Name: CVE-2018-17665
Description: This vulnerability allows remote attackers to execute arbitrary code on vulnerable installations of Foxit Reader 9.2.0.9297. User interaction is required to exploit this vulnerability in that the target must visit a malicious page or open a malicious file. The specific flaw exists within the handling of the currentPage property of a Host object. The issue results from the lack of validating the existence of an object prior to performing operations on the object. An attacker can leverage this vulnerability to execute code in the context of the current process. Was ZDI-CAN-6519.

Name: CVE-2018-17765
Description: Ingenico Telium 2 POS terminals have undeclared TRACE protocol commands. This is fixed in Telium 2 SDK v9.32.03 patch N.

Name: CVE-2018-17766
Description: Ingenico Telium 2 POS Telium2 OS allow bypass of file-reading restrictions via the NTPT3 protocol. This is fixed in Telium 2 SDK v9.32.03 patch N.

Name: CVE-2018-17767
Description: Ingenico Telium 2 POS terminals have hardcoded PPP credentials. This is fixed in Telium 2 SDK v9.32.03 patch N.

Name: CVE-2018-17768
Description: Ingenico Telium 2 POS terminals have an insecure TRACE protocol. This is fixed in Telium 2 SDK v9.32.03 patch N.

Name: CVE-2018-17769
Description: Ingenico Telium 2 POS terminals have a buffer overflow via the 0x26 command of the NTPT3 protocol. This is fixed in Telium 2 SDK v9.32.03 patch N.

Name: CVE-2018-1777
Description: IBM WebSphere Application Server 7.0, 8.0, 8.5, and 9.0 is vulnerable to cross-site scripting. This vulnerability allows users to embed arbitrary JavaScript code in the Web UI thus altering the intended functionality potentially leading to credentials disclosure within a trusted session. IBM X-Force ID: 148800.

Name: CVE-2018-17770
Description: Ingenico Telium 2 POS terminals have a buffer overflow via the RemotePutFile command of the NTPT3 protocol. This is fixed in Telium 2 SDK v9.32.03 patch N.

Name: CVE-2018-17771
Description: Ingenico Telium 2 POS terminals have hardcoded FTP credentials. This is fixed in Telium 2 SDK v9.32.03 patch N.

Name: CVE-2018-17772
Description: Ingenico Telium 2 POS terminals allow arbitrary code execution via the TRACE protocol. This is fixed in Telium 2 SDK v9.32.03 patch N.

Name: CVE-2018-17773
Description: Ingenico Telium 2 POS terminals have a buffer overflow via SOCKET_TASK in the NTPT3 protocol. This is fixed in Telium 2 SDK v9.32.03 patch N.

Name: CVE-2018-17774
Description: Ingenico Telium 2 POS terminals have an insecure NTPT3 protocol. This is fixed in Telium 2 SDK v9.32.03 patch N.

Name: CVE-2018-17775
Description: Seqrite End Point Security v7.4 has "Everyone: (F)" permission for %PROGRAMFILES%\Seqrite\Seqrite, which allows local users to gain privileges by replacing an executable file with a Trojan horse.

Name: CVE-2018-17776
Description: PCProtect Anti-Virus v4.8.35 has "Everyone: (F)" permission for %PROGRAMFILES(X86)%\PCProtect, which allows local users to gain privileges by replacing an executable file with a Trojan horse.
